 {
  "1": "Un joueur sénégalais choisi en 10e position lors de la draft NBA : la consécration de Malo H et son passage chez les Suns de Phoenix",
  "2": "Le jeune joueur Sénégalais, âgé de 18 ans et mesurant deux mètres 18, a été choisi en 10e position lors de la draft NBA. Malo H, un des plus suivis par les observateurs, s'est déjà illustré à plusieurs reprises dans trois éditions de la Balle aux Jeux Olympiques et a fréquenté les rangs de l'académie de la NBA à Sali. Maintenant qu'il est choisi par les Houston Rockets, ce qui ont immédiatement échangé avec les Suns de Phoenix au moment de l'annoncé, Malo H ne peut retenir ses larmes : « C'est un jour si spécial pour moi, un jour que je n'oublierai jamais ». Cette consécration est une preuve que le rêve peut devenir réalité quelque part dans le monde, et Malo H est impatient de porter le maillot des Suns avec son nom dessus.",
  "3": ["NBA Draft", "Sénégal", "Malo H", "Basket-ball", "Recrutement"],
  "4": "Sports"
}

 {
  "1": "Death toll rises to 200 in Niger State floods as rescuers search for survivors",
  "2": "The death toll from flash floods that have ravaged parts of Niger State in north-central Nigeria has risen to 200 people. Rescuers are tirelessly sifting through mud and debris searching for survivors and victims while hundreds of people remain missing. There's also growing concern over the risk of the spread of disease. In Mokwa, the hardest-hit area, at least 500 households have been affected by the floods, said to be the worst in living memory. Witnesses say that the downpour that hit Mokwa are the worst in living memory. The sudden and intense floods built up rapidly in just a few hours. Roads were washed away, hundreds of families affected and thousands displaced. Heavy machinery is aiding with efforts to recover bodies and remove debris. Many are still missing, but hopes of finding survivors have faded as authorities have halted search and rescue operations.",
  "3": ["Nigeria floods", "flash floods", "Mokwa", "death toll", "rescue operation"],
  "4": "Africa"
}

 {
  "1": "Fast Fashion Waste Crisis: The Atacama Desert Becomes a Dumping Ground",
  "2": "Chile's duty-free port in Iquique has become a hub for fast fashion exports, leading to an overproduction of clothes. With no legal landfills for textile waste, most of these clothes end up in the Atacama Desert, the driest place on Earth. This has led to environmental degradation and health issues for local residents. The EU is working towards implementing regulations to tackle this issue at its root, including making fashion brands responsible for their waste and requiring a digital passport for goods sold within the block.",
  "3": ["Fast Fashion", "Textile Waste", "Atacama Desert", "Chile", "Environment"],
  "4": "Environment"
}

